<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Leeds have announced the signing of Diego Llorente from Real Sociedad.</p>

<p>The 27-year-old defender has joined in a deal worth up to £20million and signed a four-year deal at Elland Road. </p>

<p>Llorente, who will wear the No 14 shirt, has become the second Spain international to join Leeds this summer with the club having already secured Rodrigo from Valencia. </p>

<p>Leeds have announced the signing of defender Diego Llorente from Real Sociedad</p>

<p>The defender spent the early part of his career at Real Madrid, but only made three appearances for the first team. </p>

<p>Instead he often played in youth squads or out on loan at Rayo Vallecano and Malaga.</p>

<p>He joined Real Sociedad in 2017, and has since made 88 appearances for the club, scoring eight goals in that time. </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>
